        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Cincini</placeName>
                <date>Oct. 9</date>.</p>
            <p>Rd. Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Herewith I enclose the conclusion of the rejoinder to <persName>D.
                    Wise</persName><lb/> my last correspodena<add>?</add> with you, was written
                during the confusion caused by removing into our <add>?</add><lb/> House on
                    <placeName>8th St.</placeName> from our <sic>cuntry</sic> retreat. I should have
                mentioned to you and also<lb/> noticed it in my article. One of the causes that
                urged me to the attempt of agitating<lb/> a call for a conference. In a private
                conversation with a wealthy and influential<lb/> person of our city, he remarks that
                if he were capable to write his sentiments, concer<lb/>ning some of the doubtful
                questions <del>of</del> that now agitate the public mind, he would<lb/> try hard to
                get a conference composed of competent men, that would give their final<lb/> verdict
                and satisfy all parties, he would <sic>cheerfuly</sic> subscribe 500$ toward the
                expenses<lb/> connecting it &amp; &amp;, but as this was private I withhold his
                name. I have in this last, <sic>referd</sic> to<lb/> a meeting lately held in lodge
                L., a two third was taken on the question of abolishing the 2d<lb/> holiday it was
                carried to abolish 63. to reclaim 31 The Doctor is now going through the<lb/> City
                canvasing for Signatures to pledge their names that they will close their<lb/>
                business on <date>Sab.</date> I hope he may succeed, as yet he has but few names,
                    <add>?</add><lb/> he has not carried out any of his proposed measures. I have
                    <sic>endeavord</sic> in my<lb/> humble manner to show the character of the new
                minag. and to caution<lb/> the public against its adoption, if you will endorse this
                or give the sentences a<lb/> better expression, so much the better. I have put my
                name <del>at</del> and that of <hi rend="underline"
                    ><placeName>Cincin</placeName></hi><lb/> at the conclusion. 513 alone would do,
                but I wish it known, that there are numbers<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> who condemn the course <sic>persued</sic> by
                the Dr. &amp; his colleagues, nor do<lb/> they allow his paper to be
                    <sic>considerd</sic> their Organ please to notice this, <persName>Mr. P.
                    Bamberger</persName><lb/> says if you will send his a/c on, he will discharge
                it. I have filed the weekly Occident<lb/> The whole of them did not reach me, I have
                collected the missing <hi rend="underline">numbers</hi>. I am short of<lb/> No. 10.
                Could you send this on and charge it—</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">In haste</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours Very Respy</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Saml. Bruel</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <sic>
                        <addressee>Revd I Leesor</addressee>
                    </sic>
                </hi>
            </p>
